HEADWORD: Hares-tail
<hw>Hare's"-tail`</hw> <pr>(-t⟦amac⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A kind of grass (<spn>Eriophorum
vaginatum</spn>). See <cref>Cotton grass</cref>, under
<er>Cotton</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hare's-tail grass</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a
species of grass (<spn>Lagurus ovatus</spn>) whose head resembles a
hare's tail.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harfang</ent>⟦br⟧
